# Performance Rules

## Image optimisation
```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

// Always use next/image for layout images
<Image
  src="/toys/bear.webp"
  alt="Handmade crochet bear toy"
  width={600}
  height={600}
  priority={isAboveFold}    // true only for hero/LCP image
  loading={isAboveFold ? "eager" : "lazy"}
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 50vw, 33vw"
/>
```

## Video (hero background)
```tsx
<video
  autoPlay
  muted
  loop
  playsInline
  preload="metadata"           // not "auto"
  aria-hidden="true"
>
  <source src="/video/hero-ambient.webm" type="video/webm" />
  <source src="/video/hero-ambient.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
</video>
```

## Dynamic imports
```tsx
// All heavy components must be lazy
const HandwovenSoulsStage3D = dynamic(
  () => import("@/components/3d/HandwovenSoulsStage3D"),
  { ssr: false, loading: () => <div className={styles.stage3dPlaceholder} /> }
);

// Use IntersectionObserver to defer canvas mount until near-viewport
```

## Font loading (already configured in layout.tsx)
- `display: "swap"` on all Google Fonts
- Preload only the display font (Cormorant Garamond 300/400/500)
- Body font (Inter) can load after paint

## CSS performance
- `will-change: transform` — only on elements actively being GSAP-animated
- Remove `will-change` after animation: `el.style.willChange = "auto"`
- Avoid `backdrop-filter` on >3 overlapping elements (GPU overdraw)
- Use `contain: layout` on sections that don't affect each other

## JavaScript bundle targets
- Main bundle (page load): < 150kb gzipped
- React + Next.js runtime: ~90kb (fixed)
- GSAP: ~25kb gzipped
- Lenis: ~5kb gzipped
- Three.js + R3F: loaded only when canvas enters viewport (~250kb — acceptable as async)

## Core Web Vitals checklist
- **LCP**: Hero image/video must have `priority` + `preload`; use `<link rel="preload">` for hero font
- **CLS**: All images need explicit `width` + `height`; avoid inserting DOM above existing content; use CSS `aspect-ratio`
- **INP**: Event handlers must complete < 200ms; heavy computation → `requestIdleCallback` or Worker
- **TTFB**: Static export on Cloudflare Pages CDN → inherently fast; no SSR wait

## Monitoring
Check `.lighthouse/` baselines before and after major changes:
```bash
npx lighthouse http://localhost:3000 --output=json --output-path=.lighthouse/latest.json
```

## Bundle analysis
```bash
ANALYZE=true npm run build   # if next-bundle-analyzer is configured
# Or manually inspect: ls -la .next/static/chunks/
```
